                  <coding>
                     <system value="http://loinc.org"/>
                     <code value="8648-8"/>
                     <display value="Hospital course note"/>
                  </coding>
               </code>
               <text>
                  <status value="generated"/>
                  <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Dear colleague, I am writing to inform you regarding your patient, an 18-year-old male admitted on 29/03/2017 following a knee injury. Clinical examination revealed medial instability of the right knee. MRI confirmed a complete tear of the medial collateral ligament (MCL). Following orthopaedic assessment, the patient underwent surgical MCL repair on 30/03/2017 under general anaesthesia. The procedure was uncomplicated, and post-operative recovery was uneventful. Post-operative physiotherapy instructions and a hinged knee brace have been provided. The patient was discharged on 31/03/2017 with analgesia and instructions for gradual weight-bearing mobilisation. Follow-up in our orthopaedic outpatient clinic is scheduled in two weeks. Please monitor wound healing and ensure adherence to the rehabilitation programme. Should you have any concerns, do not hesitate to contact our department.</div>
               </text>
            </section>
